Detailed Description

Description:
: Advance a property enumerator to the next entry. 
           TEE_Result TEE_GetNextProperty(
               TEE_PropSetHandle enumerator);

           For this test, we will need at least one TA.

           Pre:
           Open a session to a GPTA.

           Post:
           Close session and check that it succeeds.

Function Documentation

TestCase_GC001_AdvanceToEnd ( )
Trusted Applications dependencies:
none
Focus:
Test the functionality of TEE_GetNextProperty().
Test Steps:
Call TEE_AllocatePropertyEnumerator to get a new enumerator for TEE_PROPSET_TEE_IMPLEMENTATION In a loop until TEE_GetNextProperty() returns TEE_ERROR_ITEM_NOT_FOUND:
  • Call TEE_GetPropertyName() with length 0, and buffer=NULL which should return TEE_ERROR_SHORT_BUFFER and the length needed for the name
  • allocate a buffer using the length from the previous call
  • call TEE_GetPropertyName() with the newly-allocated buffer
  • verify that each name is different from the previous one
  • call TEE_GetNextProperty() Check that at least 5 different properties were retrieved Call TEE_FreePropertyEnumerator() on the previously-allocated enumerators
Manual Execution:
No

Yes
